                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/1–1049: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Major General <persName type="from">Patrick J.
                            Hurley</persName> to President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="77" xml:id="d504fn77">Transmitted through military channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-17">17 November,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Replying to your Number 121. I am grateful to you for your offer to appoint me
                    Ambassador to China. I accept the appointment with a full realization of its
                    significance in the present critical situation.</p>
                <closer>[<signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hurley</hi>
                    </signed>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
